27年","1326":"1326年","1269":"1269年","1258":"1258年","1224":"1224年","1245":"1245年","1254":"1254年","1375":"1375年","about 1269":"大约1269年","1317":"1317年","Garthorpe, Leicestershire, England":"英国英格兰萊希斯特斯爾加索普","Mowsley, Leicestershire, England":"英国英格兰萊希斯特斯爾莫福斯利","Eastwell, Leics, Eng":"英国英格兰萊希斯特斯爾易亞斯特維爾","lifeSummary":"当Mathew Brabazon于1254年出生在英国英格兰萊希斯特斯爾莫福斯利时，他的父亲Roger le BRABAZON34岁，母亲Beatrix Bissett30岁。他于大约1271年与Mrs. Sarah Brabazon在英国英格兰萊希斯特斯爾加索普结婚。他们至少是2个儿子的父母。他去世于1317年在英国英格兰萊希斯特斯爾加索普享年63岁。"},"hr":{"1254–1317":"1254.–1317.","1242–1295":"1242–1295","1258–Male":"1258–preminuo","1245–1326":"1245–1326","1269–1375":"1269–1375","1275–1327":"1275.–1327","1220–Male":"1220–preminuo","1224–Female":"1224–preminula","about 1271":"oko 1271.","1275":"1275.","1220":"1220","1242":"1242","1295":"1295","1327":"1327","1326":"1326","1269":"1269","1258":"1258","1224":"1224","1245":"1245","1254":"1254.","1375":"1375","about 1269":"oko 1269.","1317":"1317.","Garthorpe, Leicestershire, England":"Garthorpe, Leicestershire, Engleska, United Kingdom","Mowsley, Leicestershire, England":"Mowsley, Leicestershire, Engleska, United Kingdom","Eastwell, Leics, Eng":"Eastwell, Leicestershire, Engleska, United Kingdom"},"cs":{"1254–1317":"1254–1317","1242–1295":"1242–1295","1258–Male":"1258–Zesnulý","1245–1326":"1245–1326","1269–1375":"1269–1375","1275–1327":"1275–1327","1220–Male":"1220–Zesnulý","1224–Female":"1224–Zesnulá","about 1271":"okolo 1271","1275":"1275","1220":"1220","1242":"1242","1295":"1295","1327":"1327","1326":"1326","1269":"1269","1258":"1258","1224":"1224","1245":"1245","1254":"1254","1375":"1375","about 1269":"okolo 1269","1317":"1317","Garthorpe, Leicestershire, England":"Garthorpe, Leicestershire, Anglie, United Kingdom","Mowsley, Leicestershire, England":"Mowsley, Leicestershire, Anglie, United Kingdom","Eastwell, Leics, Eng":"Eastwell, Leicestershire, Anglie, United Kingdom"},"da":{"1254–1317":"1254–1317","1242–1295":"1242–1295","1258–Male":"1258–Afdød","1245–1326":"1245–1326","1269–1375":"1269–1375","1275–1327":"1275–1327","1220–Male":"1220–Afdød","1224–Female":"1224–Afdød","about 1271":"omkring 1271","1275":"1275","1220":"1220","1242":"1242","1295":"1295","1327":"1327","1326":"1326","1269":"1269","1258":"1258","1224":"1224","1245":"1245","1254":"1254","1375":"1375","about 1269":"omkring 1269","1317":"1317","Garthorpe, Leicestershire, England":"Garthorpe, Leicestershire, England, United Kingdom","Mowsley, Leicestershire, England":"Mowsley, Leicestershire, England, United Kingdom","Eastwell, Leics, Eng":"Eastwell, Leicestershire, England, United Kingdom"},"nl":{"1254–1317":"1254–1317","1242–1295":"1242–1295","1258–Male":"1258–Overleden","1245–1326":"1245–1326","1269–1375":"1269–1375","1275–1327":"1275–1327","1220–Male":"1220–Overleden","1224–Female":"1224–Overleden","about 1271":"circa 1271","1275":"1275","1220":"1220","1242":"1242","1295":"1295","1327":"1327","1326":"1326","1269":"1269","1258":"1258","1224":"1224","1245":"1245","1254":"1254","1375":"1375","about 1269":"circa 1269","1317":"1317","Garthorpe, Leicestershire, England":"Garthorpe, Leicestershire, Engeland, Verenigd Koninkrijk","Mowsley, Leicestershire, England":"Mowsley, Leicestershire, Engeland, Verenigd Koninkrijk","Eastwell, Leics, Eng":"Eastwell, Leicestershire, Engeland, Verenigd Koninkrijk"},"en":{"1254–1317":"1254–1317","1242–1295":"1242–1295","1258–Male":"1258–Deceased","1245–1326":"1245–1326","1269–1375":"1269–1375","1275–1327":"1275–1327","1220–Male":"1220–Deceased","1224–Female":"1224–Deceased","about 1271":"about 1271","1275":"1275","1220":"1220","1242":"1242","1295":"1295","1327":"1327","1326":"1326","1269":"1269","1258":"1258","1224":"1224","1245":"1245","1254":"1254","1375":"1375","about 1269":"about 1269","1317":"1317","Garthorpe, Leicestershire, England":"Garthorpe, Leicestershire, England, United Kingdom","Mowsley, Leicestershire, England":"Mowsley, Leicestershire, England, United Kingdom","Eastwell, Leics, Eng":"Eastwell, Leicestershire, England, United Kingdom","nameMeanings":[{"name":"Brabazon","type":"LAST","attribution":"Dictionary of American Family Names © Patrick Hanks 2003, 2006.","meanings":["English: from Old French <i>Brabançon</i>, Anglo-Norman French <i>Brabanzon</i>, Middle English <i>Brab(a)son</i> ‘Brabanter’. This was originally an ethnic name for a native of the duchy of Brabant (now in north Belgium). Medieval Brabant was widely known for two exports, its brutal mercenary soldiers and its linen cloth. In the 13th century parts of France were devastated by marauding gangs of armed Brabanters, and <i>brabançon</i> came to be used generically to denote a mercenary, hired assassin, or robber. These originated in Brabant and Flanders, but in the course of time accepted recruits from anywhere. The true source of the surname is the presence in many English (and Irish) towns of Brabant cloth merchants."],"variants":[{"name":"Bravender","meanings":["English (East Yorkshire): ethnic name for someone from Brabant (Flanders). Compare   Brabazon  ."]},{"name":"Brabson","meanings":["English (Warwickshire): variant of   Brabazon  . This form is now rare in Britain."]},{"name":"Brabant","meanings":["Some characteristic forenames:  French Aime, Aristide, Marcel, Normand, Ovila, Yvan.","French, Walloon, Flemish, and German: habitational name from Brabant, a province in the Low Countries.","English: cognate of 1 above, from Old French <i>Brabant</i>, Middle English <i>Braban</i>, <i>Brabayn</i>, used to denote both the region and an inhabitant of it. See also the synonymous   Brabazon  . In medieval England, Brabans were typically linen weavers and cloth merchants. The final syllable of <i>Braban</i>, when weakly stressed, was often altered to <i>-ben</i>, <i>-bin</i>, or <i>-bon</i>, and also to <i>-bam</i>. The additional <i>-t</i> or <i>-d</i> in post-medieval <i>Brabant</i>,   Braband  , etc. is probably excrescent, rather than a relic of the Old French form."]}]},{"name":"Mathew","type":"FIRST","attribution":"Dictionary of First Names © Patrick Hanks and Flavia Hodges 1990, 2003, 2006.","meanings":["Variant spelling of   Matthew ."],"variants":[{"name":"Matthew","meanings":["form of the name of the Christian evangelist, author of the first gospel in the New Testament. His name is a form of the Hebrew name <i>Mattathia</i>, meaning ‘gift of God’, which is fairly common in the Old Testament, being rendered in the Authorized Version in a number of different forms: <i>Mattan(i)ah</i>, <i>Mattatha(h)</i>, <i>Mattithiah</i>, <i>Mattathias</i>, and so on. In the Authorized Version, the evangelist is regularly referred to as <i>Matthew</i>, while the apostle chosen to replace Judas Iscariot is distinguished as   Matthias .  A related name from the same Hebrew roots, but reversed, is   Jonathan .  Throughout the English-speaking world <i>Matthew</i> has been particularly popular since the 1970s."]}]}],"lifeSummary":"When Mathew Brabazon was born in 1254, in Mowsley, Leicestershire, England, United Kingdom, his father, Roger le BRABAZON, was 34 and his mother, Beatrix Bissett, was 30. He married Mrs. Sarah Brabazon about 1271, in Garthorpe, Leicestershire, England, United Kingdom. They were the parents of at least 2 sons. He died in 1317, in Garthorpe, Leicestershire, England, United Kingdom, at the age of 63."},"et":{"1254–1317":"1254–1317","1242–1295":"1242–1295","1258–Male":"1258–Surnud","1245–1326":"1245–1326","1269–1375":"1269–1375","1275–1327":"1275–1327","1220–Male":"1220–Surnud","1224–Female":"1224–Surnud","about 1271":"umbes 1271","1275":"1275","1220":"1220","1242":"1242","1295":"1295","1327":"1327","1326":"1326","1269":"1269","1258":"1258","1224":"1224","1245":"1245","1254":"1254","1375":"1375","about 1269":"umbes 1269","1317":"1317","Garthorpe, Leicestershire, England":"Garthorpe, Leicestershire, Inglismaa, United Kingdom","Mowsley, Leicestershire, England":"Mowsley, Leicestershire, Inglismaa, United Kingdom","Eastwell, Leics, Eng":"Eastwell, Leicestershire, Inglismaa, United K